Kaltura is a media sharing platform similar to YouTube. They have a hosted version as well as a couple self hosted versions. It would be nice to be able to embed Kaltura videos in a similar way as the YouTube connector works. This would give companies the ability to host video content that can be embedded in Confluence without having to rely on an outside service to host the videos ... especially if the video content if private or confidential. Confluence is great as a wiki, but really not so great as a media sharing platform. It would be awesome to be able to combine these two great platforms together so that you folks can focus on what you do well ... and this creating a great wiki platform.

