I would really like to see Confluence have the ability to automatically remove older historical versions of pages automatically.  Allow the user to set a retention time period, 1 yr, 2 yr, 3 yr, 5 yr, etc. and have the system delete any pages in history that are older on a set time schedule (daily, weekly, monthly).

Our company has a 3 yr retention policy for legal purposes and right now there is no easy way to delete history from Confluence.  We use it to store  documents and information. 

Additionally, this would help keep the database a little more fit and trim.

